### What is changed and how it works?

Issue Number: Close #13673 

What's Changed:

- Move reconnect logic to one single coroutine `reconnect_loop`
- Move streaming RPCs to individual long-running coroutines that are not destroyed even when connection is rebuilt
- All client methods take mutable
```yaml
pub fn hearbeat(&self) -> Sender {
        let (tx, rx) = tikv_util::futures::bounded();
        let client = self.cached_client.clone();
        self.rpc_client.spawn(async move {
            loop {
                client.latest().wait_for_ready().await;
                let (g_tx, g_rx) = client.heartbeat();
                select!(g_tx.send_all(rx).await, g_rx);
            }
        });
     }
```

